  "prompt": "Can Google help me track my lost Android phone by the IMEI number?",
  "response": "Google does not directly provide a service to track a lost Android phone using the IMEI number. However, you can use Google's \"Find My Device\" service, which allows you to locate, lock, or erase your lost Android phone, provided that the phone is connected to your Google account, turned on, and has an active internet connection.\n\nHere's what you can do to try to locate your lost Android phone:\n\n1. **Find My Device**: Go to the Find My Device website (https://www.google.com/android/find) and sign in with your Google account. If your phone is online, you will be able to see its location, make it ring, lock it, or erase its data.\n\n2. **Google Maps Timeline**: Check your Google Maps Timeline (https://www.google.com/maps/timeline) to see if your phone's last location was recorded before it went offline.\n\nIf these methods are unsuccessful and you believe your phone has been stolen, you might try the following:\n\n- **Report to the Police**: Provide them with your phone's IMEI number, which is a unique identifier for your device. Law enforcement may be able to use this information to help recover your phone.\n\n- **Carrier Support**: Contact your mobile carrier. They may be able to block your phone from accessing their network based on the IMEI number, which can prevent the device from being used by someone else.\n\nRemember that taking preventive measures, such as regularly backing up your data and using security features, can help protect your information in case your device is lost or stolen.",
